result.execSummary:
The defendant Megan Ann Cornell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Compliance with the Marinette County Treatment Drug Court Program.

If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.

miscConds.notes:
May not vote or serve on a jury until civil rights are restored.
No firearms.
Provide DNA sample & pay surcharge.

No contact with co-defendant(s).
No possession or consumption of alcohol or illegal drugs.
No possession of drug paraphernalia.
May not be in taverns or bars or on any premises licensed for the sale of intoxicating beverages, except restaurants and grocery stores.
No contact with known drug users or drug houses.

Complete AODA assessment and any recommended treatment and aftercare and any other counseling as recommended by agent or determined by Drug Court.
Completion of a cognitive intervention program.
